p: The extract and fractions from A. tenuifolius were previously analyzed by LC-DAD-MS, and some constituents could be annotated [ 25]. Thus, we reanalyzed them to expand the annotation of the constituents using GNPS library and data reported in the literature ( Figure 1, Table 1); moreover, the data were applied to create the molecular network from their constituents and so determine the goal compounds from the most active fraction AS-AT ( Figure 2). The molecular formulae of the constituents from AS-AT were determined based on the mass errors up ±10 ppm and mSigma below 30.
